title: USD 800 billion Emergency Economic Stabilization Act draft 28 Se
description:
Summary
Sep 28, 2008 draft federal bill, the so-called Emergency Economic Stabilization Act, 2008. The draft bill gives approximately $800 Billion dollars in tax revenue to the financial services industry in the United States ,which has recently undergone a series of spectacular collapses. House speaker Nanci Pelosi (D), stated that the draft would be available on http://speaker.house.gov and http://financialservices.house.gov, however, possibly due to world-wide interest, both sites have been unavailable since at least the time of the announcement.
